lines.text: Let's Incorporate! Or, do you want me to go back on the open market?
Well, I couldn't become a stockholder right now.
Then take an option on me for 30 days.
Sorry, but when I make that kind of a deposit, I want to own the stock out right. Goodbye...
I'm going up to a lumber camp and marry a chef.
What? You're going to a lumber camp? And get yourself all full of splinters?
Well if I do I can always get myself a woodpecker.
Your physical condition is your apprenticeship. My order as physician is to strip.
For somersaults and tailspins I have to test your nerves. I must see just how good you are on curves.
Oh, we're very good on curves.
Oh Rusty, here I am, all dressed up and no place to go. Nobody loves me. Oh, why was I ever born?
